{
  "texts": [
    "The default settings of LLMs are the same, using nucleus sampling [24] with 𝑡𝑜𝑝_𝑝=0.95, 𝑡𝑒𝑚𝑝𝑒𝑟𝑎𝑡𝑢𝑟𝑒=0.8, and 10 samples per translation.",
    "Besides, we design a Basic Prompt to evaluate LLMs' code translation capability, which can be formally defined as \"Given ${𝑝𝑙 𝑠𝑟𝑐 } code:\\n${𝑝𝑟𝑜𝑔 𝑠𝑟𝑐 }\\nTranslate given ${𝑝𝑙 𝑠𝑟𝑐 } code to ${𝑝𝑙 𝑡𝑎𝑟 } code.",
    "Use END_OF_CASE to finish your answer. \"",
    "An example of the Basic Prompt and a generated result is shown in Figure 7.",
    "In experiments, we adopt a one-shot learning setting to make every LLM understand more about the task and only evaluate their first outputs."
  ]
}